Metric: Monthly Churn Rate
Description: Percentage of active subscribers at the start of the month who canceled or did not renew by month end. Excludes plan downgrades and trial expirations.
Owner: growth-team
Tags: churn, retention, saas, monthly

Source: subscriptions, subscription_events

Given the subscription was active at the start of the month
  And the subscription is not a free trial
  And the customer has been active for at least one full billing cycle

When we calculate
  Then count subscriptions that transitioned to "canceled" or "expired" during the month
  And divide by the total active subscriptions at the start of the month
  And multiply by 100 to express as a percentage

The result is "Monthly Churn Rate"

Trust:
  Freshness must be less than 12 hours
  Null rate on status must be less than 0%
  Null rate on canceled_at must be less than 2%
  Row count of subscriptions must not drop more than 10% day over day
  Value must be between 0 and 25
  Value must not change more than 30% month over month
